In [32]:
sns.pairplot(df1[['Auction', 'Color', 'IsBadBuy', 'MMRCurrentAuctionAveragePrice', 'Size',
       'TopThreeAmericanName', 'VehBCost', 'VehicleAge', 'VehOdo',
       'WarrantyCost', 'WheelType']],hue='IsBadBuy')
Out[32]:
<seaborn.axisgrid.PairGrid at 0x7fc9a6c4c490>

By adding the parameter hue='IsBadBuy' helps tremendously to see which aspects are bad buys or not. We see on the legend that orange colored graphs are not bad buys, and blue are bad buys.
